		<a name="56984"></a>
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;08/07/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 20:32:49</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=3429"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=3429')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=56984&amp;TOPIC_ID=6927&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Verants+answer+to+DOT+Stacking+on+the+Faire&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Folks beneficial spells may use similar mechantics to DoTs, but if you sift through the available spell fields you will see that Verant can easily differentiate between detrimental and beneficial spell lines.</P><P>This is how Extended Affliction focus items do not work for Celestial Healing and such.</P><P>The issue with stacking is having to dynamically append a unique identifyer to DoT effects.  For example, when cast Cascading Darkess becomes effect: Cascading_Darkness_ANDS20983.  Verant has already created a unique identifier for all players beyond that of their Station ID.  This PID or Player Identification Number, could, in theory, be appended to the effect when it lands on a critter.  Doing so would both allow multiple necromancers to cast the same DoT and prevent a single necromancer from stacking 5 Envenomed Bolts on the same critter.</P><P>Would it change EQ...yes.  Raid leaders would need to figure out what detrimental effects they wanted on a given Mob.  Given that there are 15 slots, 5 necromancers on a raid would use them all up easily.  Do I see this as a problem?  Heck no, justs adds another layer of strategy to the mix.</P><P>DoT stacking is doable; the question is will it be done?</P><P>ta,<BR>=sv=</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

